<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-07-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-07-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="491" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d491">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 365.117/378</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-07-06">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 6, 1916</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>663. Department’s 532, April 21. Military authorities refuse release
                            Angelo Mazzei claiming if he lost Italian citizenship during his
                            minority, in consequence father’s naturalization, nevertheless, he would
                            have been obliged perform military service in accordance provisions
                            Article 12, Civil Code, which was in force when his class 88 was
                            called.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
